ca are in the public domain or have no known copyright restrictions.  Newspapers published in the United States more than 95 years ago are in the public domain in their entirety. Any newspapers in Chronicling America that were published less than 95 years ago are also believed to be in the public domain, but may contain some copyrighted third party materials. Researchers using newspapers published less than 95 years ago should be alert for modern content (for example, registered and renewed for copyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 13.655856, "shard": "09", "shelf_id": "sn88064250, 1907-11-23, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/lu", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["opelousas", "saint landry", "united states", "louisiana", "opelousas (la.)", "newspapers"], "subject_headings": ["Opelousas (La.)--Newspapers", "Louisiana--Opelousas", "United States--Louisiana--Saint Landry--Opelousas"], "subjects": [{"louisiana": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:louisiana&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"opelousas": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:opelousas&fo=json"}, {"opelousas (la.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:opelousas+%28la.%29&fo=json"}, {"saint landry": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:saint+landry&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2023-05-11T06:17:30.821Z", "title": "St. Landry clarion (Opelousas, La.), November 23, 1907", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn88064250/1907-11-23/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn88064250/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn88064250"], "batch": ["lu_jacobi_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1890", "description": ["Weekly Vol. 1, no. 1 (Oct. 11, 1890)-v. 32, no. 4 (Nov. 19, 1921). Available on microfilm from Louisiana State University Library. Archived issues are available in digital format as part of the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. In English and French, Nov. 22, 1890-<Apr. 30, 1892>. Star-progress (DLC)sn 88064249 (OCoLC)17616419 Clarion-progress (DLC)sn 88064251 (OCoLC)17616382"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:00.253Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "catalog-split-02", "catalog", "ndnp/newspapers", "main-catalog-split-02", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn88064250/", "image_url": [], "index": 8, "language": ["french", "english"], "latlong": [30.5257248, -92.0842759], "location": ["united states", "louisiana", "saint landry", "opelousas"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-92.0842759, 30.5257248], "number": ["original", "univ of virginia", "sn88064251", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2332-5429", "tulane univ", "sn88064249", "bayouland reg newsp group", "sn88064250", "2025-06-25t14:24:21", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn88064250/1890-10-11/ed-1/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn88064250/1921-11-19/ed-1/", "mcneese state univ", "online resource", "microfilm master", "2020-10-07t17:01:08.640667", "1527", "louisiana state univ", "1", "17616440", "microfilm service copy"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Saint Landry clarion", "Clarion"], "partof": ["chronicling america", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division", "catalog", "st. landry clarion (opelousas, la.) 1890-1921"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 61.634968, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "catalog", "usnd"], "subject": ["opelousas", "saint landry", "united states", "louisiana", "opelousas (la.)", "newspapers"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:26:17.806Z", "title": "St. Landry clarion.", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn88064250/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2013272163/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["spencer, william h.", "compton, t. g.", "meynier, andrew", "sandoz, leonce", "jones, d. j.", "sandoz, joel h.", "sandoz, l. a."], "date": "1852", "dates": ["[1852 TO 1910]"], "description": ["Weekly, <July 25, 1863>-<Feb. 5, 1910> Began with Vol. 1, no. 1 (December 11, 1852). Ceased in 1910? Published with an additional masthead in French: Le Courrier des Opelousas, 1852-June 23, 1883. Publishers: Joel Sandoz & Andrew Meynier, 1852-1857; Joel Sandoz, 1858-1861; Joel H. Sandoz & William H. Spencer, 1862-1863; William Curran, 1863; Leonce & L.A. Sandoz, 1863-1867; Joel H. Sandoz, 1867-1870; Leonce Sandoz, 1871-1877; Leonce & L.A. Sandoz, 1878-1890; Leonce Sandoz, 1891-1894; Leonce & L.A. Sandoz, 1895; L.A. Sandoz, 1896; Leonce Sandoz, 1897-1907; Courier Pub. Co., 1908-1910. Some issues printed on wallpaper, 1862-1864. <Apr. 22-30>, 1863 issues edited by occupying Union forces. Editors: T.G. Compton, <1867>; D.J. Jones, <1873>; L.A. Sandoz, <1896>. Publisher: Estate of Leonce Sandoz <February 1910>. Suspended in May 1863? Resumed with July 25, 1863 issue. Suspended with Mar. 12, 1864 issue? Resumed with May 14, 1864 issue. Suspended with Apr. 23, 1870 issue; resumed with Aug. 6, 1870. In English and French, 1852-<Aug. 29, 1903>. Description based on: Vol. 1, no. 1 (December 11, 1852); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 4, 2013). Latest issue consulted: Vol. 57, no. 29 (February 5, 1910) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 4, 2013)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:24.080Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2013272163/", "image_url": [], "index": 9, "language": ["french", "english"], "location": ["united states", "louisiana", "saint landry", "opelousas"], "number": ["862979190", "2013272163", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource", "2332-5372"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Courrier des Opelousas"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the opelousas courier (opelousas, louisiana) 1852-1910 [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 52.427742, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["opelousas", "saint landry", "united states", "louisiana", "opelousas (la.)", "newspapers"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:49:47.660Z", "title": "The Opelousas courier", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2013272163/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2013272166/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1890", "dates": ["[1890 TO 1921]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with vol. I, no. 1 (October 11, 1890); ceased with vol. XXXII, no. 4 (Nov. 19, 1921). Publisher: The Clarion Company, Ltd., <November 1921>. In English and French, Nov. 22, 1890-<Apr. 30, 1892>. Description based on: Vol. I, no. 1 (October 11, 1890); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 4, 2013). Latest issue consulted: Vol. XXXII, no. 4 (Nov. 19, 1921) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 4, 2013). Star-progress (Online) Clarion-progress (Online)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:24.080Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2013272166/", "image_url": [], "index": 10, "language": ["french", "english"], "location": ["united states", "louisiana", "saint landry", "opelousas"], "number": ["2013272166", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2332-5437", "online resource", "863053839"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Clarion", "Saint Landry clarion"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "st. landry clarion (opelousas, la.) 1890-1921 [online resource]"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 52.427742, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["opelousas", "saint landry", "united states", "louisiana", "opelousas (la.)", "newspapers"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:49:47.660Z", "title": "St. Landry clarion", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2013272166/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2015270567/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1917", "dates": ["[1917 TO 1921]"], "description": ["Weekly Began February 10, 1917; ceased with volume XIII, no. 4 (Nov. 9, 1921). Publisher: Price & Andrepont, <February 10, 1917->. Description based on: Volume X, no. 50 (October 4, 1919); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed October 28, 2015). Latest issue consulted: Volume XIII, no. 4 (Nov. 9, 1921) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed October 28, 2015). St. Landry clarion Clarion-progress"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:32.598Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2015270567/", "image_url": [], "index": 11, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "louisiana", "saint landry", "opelousas"], "number": ["2026-04-13t21:30:13